<P><H1 align=center>CUSTOMER EXISTING BUSINESS – CR040</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P>This screen shows any existing business for a customer located using the 
search facility.</P>
<P>If the customer has no existing business, a warning message will appear when 
entering the screen – ‘No existing business found’ and the ‘Select’ and 
‘Summary’ boxes will be greyed out</P>
<P>If the customer has existing business, a record of this will be shown in the 
main box, which shows the business type, application / account number, date 
created, amount and the status (the stage the application has reached, eg. 
customer registration).</P>
<P><H3>Select: </H3>highlight the record and click on 
‘Select’. This leads to <A href="HELP_CR030.asp">Customer Application Summary (CR030)</A>
<P></P>
<P><H3>Summary: </H3>if there is an existing record, highlight 
it and click on ‘Summary’. This leads to <A href="HELP_CR042.asp">Application Summary (CR042)</A>
<P></P>
<P><H3>New Application: </H3>if there is no existing business, 
or a new application needs to be set up, click on the ‘New Application’ button. 
Three dropdown lists will appear at the bottom of the screen:
<P></P>
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE><H3>Type of mortgage application: </H3>new loan, 
remortgage, further advance, transfer of equity
<P></P>
<P><H3>Type of buyer: </H3>first time buyer, concurrent buyer, 
subsequent buyer
<P></P>
<P><H3>Application priority: </H3>high, normal, low 
</BLOCKQUOTE>  
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>once the relevant values have been selected, 
click on ‘OK’ – this leads to <A href="HELP_CR030.asp">Customer Application Summary (CR030)</A>
<P></P>

